<p>The issue I’m running into comes into play here: This is the same code but it uses an ADIS16470_IMU, the IMU we’re currently using on our competition robot (so we can track the pitch of the robot on the charging station). When I run the simulator with this code, the simulated robot doesn’t turn.</p>
<p>The robot seems to follow the X component of the trajectory but not the Y component. It is very intriguing.</p>
